HEADWORD: Cephalotomy
<hw>Ceph`a*lot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Dissection or opening of the head.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Craniotomy; -- usually applied to
bisection of the fetal head with a saw.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cephalotribe</ent>⟦br⟧
